				<td colspan="2"><span>Top 10 Bard Issues Poll is now up.
<br />

<br />
Gonna cross post what I did on EQLive site:
<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">Alright, so I had the test the questions and details up.  I added in a few new ones, chaged some, etc.
<br />
 
<br />
You will get to vote 5 times.  This means you can vote for the same item 5 times if you feel strongly enough about it or you could vote for 5 different items (and obviously any combination of 5 votes).  At the end of the 5 votes, you will see the results of everyone elses polling.
<br />
 
<br />
The top 10 items will be choosen as our new top 10 list.
<br />
 
<br />
If (for what ever reason) the poll crashes, it's ok.  The data is saved and the poll can come up again.  It will keep its current state.  If some one hacks it, I'll have to figure out a new way to poll.
<br />
 
<br />
Go Vote: <a target="_new" href="http://68.39.9.62:8888/">http://68.39.9.62:8888/</a></span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
Just wanted to add, if your IP address can't be resolved, you wont be able to vote.  If you IP masqurade, only 1 machine behind your firewall will get a vote (for all you DSL router type people).</span></td>
