			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Top 10 Bard Issues Poll<a name="67562"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 20 04 8:50 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Here's mine,
<br />

<br />
Different Songs.  New chants are all well and fine, but this is the third set of the same chants since level 40+.  Even if we do multi-function songs like DS/Haste, but change it around, like a Rune/Regen, or a Song that amps healing or benificial spells.
<br />

<br />
DPS is a major concern.  We are on the low end of all classes, period.  Our best attack or spell caps under 1k, whereas every other class can see those with crits etc (exclude Wars)
<br />

<br />
Aggro.  Yah, I know, we aren't meant to hold aggro over melees.  But it sure would be nice to pull a mob off the cleric if all h*ll breaks loose.  Even if its something as simple as a 1 shot disc/aa that just pisses a mob off with no damage.  Kinda like Fade but backwards.  900 mana would be a steal.
<br />

<br />
Song Caps.  Honestly, the song cap is killing our effectiveness.  We dont get Foci like other classes, and our base effectivness is balanced differently than other classes.  When a song only lasts 18 secs, you want it to be stellar in nature.
<br />

<br />
Expanded Song Capability.  Do this one of two ways.  Give us a couple more long last songs (Selos, Requiem, Amp, and EB all have extra long durations, why not a couple more).  Or give us a couple more AOE songs.  Something along the Muse line, but even at 20% overhaste, +10% Caster DPS would be awesome.  Its one thing when you can add 30% to a groups DPS, its even better when you can add 10-20% to a raids.
<br />

<br />
Basically, expand what we do already, but in a new way.
<br />

<br />
Just my take.
<br />
Rappa  
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
